It may be due to any of the following reasons but not limited to: Tab Switching Screen Sharing with anyone Clicking on the escape button Computer going on Sleep (Adjust your power or sleep mode settings) Windows or Browser or any Application specific notifications (Put them in No Disturb Mode or switch them off while the quiz is on) Anything else that may result in disturbing the full-screen mode The assessment does not get terminated on the first such instance. Guidelines and Key Instructions for the Preliminary Round | Unstop Talent Park - Tech!Email: 
General Unstop Talent Park - Tech Unstop Hi Kanya Bhatt , Thank you for embarking on the Unstop Talent Park - Tech journey with us! With only a few hours left until the first preliminary round, please make sure to review the essential instructions and guidelines to tackle it smoothly. A combined score of the quiz and the coding questions will be ascertained, on the basis of which top-performing individuals will be moved to the next round. Kindly read through the following key instructions regarding the structure, timeline, and rules of the quiz and coding round rounds: Timelines & Questions: Round 1 - MCQ + Coding Assessment Online Assessment Window : 7th March 2024 2:00 PM - 8:00 PM IST Online Assessment Duration : 60 Minutes Total Questions to be answered : 21 Questions 20 MCQs and 1 problem statement ought to be solved in 60 minutes for this round. You can attempt the round anytime between the provided round window. Please ensure that you attempt the round in one sitting, as once you start the round, the timer wonâ€™t stop. You will see the Play button in the Preliminary round to initiate the assessment. While you are taking the assessment, your code and time of submission are also tracked by the system question-wise. Proctoring Related: You can attempt the assessments only on a desktop/laptop with webcam access. The assessments will be hosted in full-screen mode. Anything that disturbs the full-screen mode of the assessment is treated as a violation. It may be due to any of the following reasons but not limited to: Tab Switching Screen Sharing with anyone Clicking on the escape button Computer going on Sleep (Adjust your power or sleep mode settings) Windows or Browser or any Application specific notifications (Put them in No Disturb Mode or switch them off while the quiz is on) Anything else that may result in disturbing the full-screen mode The assessment does not get terminated on the first such instance. Only repeated violations will result in disqualification and termination of the assessment immediately. Your face will be verified before the start of the assessment from the photo that was captured during registration. Your face may be verified again during the assessment. Your face will be constantly detected and violations will be tracked and reported while the assessment is on. Eg: Two faces in front of the camera, No one in front of the camera, etc. Please note, that any participant resorting to unfair practices will be directly disqualified from the challenge. All decisions in the matter of eligibility, authenticity & final judgment will be with Unstop. All the best! Regards, Team Unstop Disclaimer: This email has been sent to you on the behalf of Unstop, the organizer of Unstop Talent Park - Tech Follow us for informative & cute content: Unstop Coin Store Proud parent of our app: Queries? IDEO Reveals: The Five Innovation Traps You Need to Sidestep

IDEO's article outlines five deadly innovation traps: lack of clear strategy, orphaned ideas, talent misalignment, flawed handoff processes, and short-term metric fixation. It emphasizes the importance of a cohesive strategy, integration of new ideas into core business, alignment of team skills with innovation goals, seamless transition from development to execution, and long-term success metrics. Avoiding these traps ensures sustainable innovation and successful implementation.

To effectively navigate innovation, organizations should also foster a culture that encourages risk-taking and supports failure as a learning process. By doing so, they can build resilience against the innovation traps identified by IDEO. Encouraging open communication, facilitating cross-functional collaboration, and maintaining a customer-centric approach can further mitigate these risks, leading to more sustainable and impactful innovations.

Meet Your New Interviewer: Navigating AI in Job Searches ğŸ¤–

As AI becomes more integrated into the hiring process, job seekers might soon find themselves being interviewed by bots.
